  <refsect1>
    <title>Description</title>

    <variablelist>

      <varlistentry>
        <term>
          <function>waffle_is_extension_in_string()</function>
        </term>
        <listitem>
          <para>
            Check if an extension is contained in a GL-style extension string.
          </para>
          <para>
            The <parameter>extension_string</parameter> must be in the format returned by
            <code>glGetString(GL_EXTENSIONS)</code>. Note that this function is not restricted to the GL extension
            string; it can also be used on the GLX and EGL extension strings.
          </para>
          <para>
            This function can be called before waffle has been successfully initialized with
            <citerefentry><refentrytitle>waffle_init</refentrytitle><manvolnum>3</manvolnum></citerefentry>.
          </para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term>
          <function>waffle_make_current()</function>
        </term>
        <listitem>
          <para>
            Bind the given <parameter>window</parameter> and <parameter>context</parameter> for rendering on the current
            thread. <parameter>window</parameter> and <parameter>context</parameter> must both have been created on the
            given <parameter>display</parameter>.
          </para>
          <para>
            This function is analogous to <function>glXMakeCurrent()</function> and
            <function>eglMakeCurrent()</function>.
          </para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term>
          <function>waffle_get_proc_address()</function>
        </term>
        <listitem>
          <para>
            On GLX, this redirects to <function>glXGetProcAddress</function>. On EGL, this redirects to
            <function>eglGetProcAddress</function>. On CGL, this function simply returns null because there is no
            <function>CGLGetProcAdress</function>. For details on this function's semantics, see the specification for
            the relevant platform:
            the <ulink url="http://www.opengl.org/registry/doc/glx1.4.pdf">GLX 1.4 Specification</ulink>,
            or the <ulink url="http://www.khronos.org/registry/egl/specs/eglspec.1.4.20110406.pdf">EGL 1.4 Specification</ulink>.
          </para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

    </variablelist>
  </refsect1>

